<br>
Also, look at it from another stand point.  Put yourself into their shoes.  We all know the mage population 45+ is slim, I am lvl 52 now and sometimes I am one of 20 mages online, WHO ARE NOT ANONY, that are 50-60.  In this case with a diminished population most people do not know what we can do.  What would you rather put your money in?  A stock you know what to expect and has a steady growth pattern, or some other stock that you have no clue of?  Also their perceptions of mages may come from when they themselves tried one and stopped playing it at lvl twenty or so as mages do not pick up in power as fast as other classes.  <br>
<br>
I ask all you mages to not give up hope, and keep at it.  Magery is an awesome life, and who can at level 40 go elsewhere other than the Dreadlands to get some pretty good experience and loot solo?  There are not many classes that can. <br>
<br>
Stew Powers<br>
